<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Rylius on 08-28-2000 06:54 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">So far, this thread isn't getting to whiney like the official EQ Forums and I hope it stays that way, however, I must say that introducing too many topics like this could lead to the whiners invading us.

That said, Muse, I've said it before, you are an invaluable resource to this game! Your maps of course stand at the forefront of important resources, however, other stuff you have done with this site have helped us all too. I hope that these forums can maintain the air they have thus far and not degenerate. 

About camping dungeons. I must admit, I haven't done or camped many dungeons. I'm a 25th lvl Paladin and never found Befallen much fun. I look forward to starting doing dungeons some day as a lot of players in my guild sing their praises.

Still, after reading some stuff on this topic, I had posted an idea for a playable dungeon that I really like. Later, someone else posted a similar description.

I won't recap the entire description, but the general idea is a dungeon is made up of one-group-at-a-time zones. Mobs do not respawn until you leave a zone after which you cannot re-enter for some very long period of time. And, in the ideal world, there would be some way to enforce a time limit on a group's stay in the zone (in case they are trying to be jerks about it and just sit there with nothing to fight).

Later I elaborated on the idea. And this I really like. Why not make the zone reproduceable. Every group that enters a particular dungeon gets an instance of that dungeon all for that group. If another group enters the same dungeon, another instance of the zone is created on the server for that group. Ok, not realistic, but would definitely give you that dungeon feel - hands down!

Be Safe and Good Hunting

Rylius</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
